title: Boyertown boys nab big win over Owen J. Roberts
text:
Boyertown boys nab big win over Owen J. Roberts Bears narrow gap for Liberty division lead Published: 11:30 PM EDT Oct 07, 2015 Boyertown nabs big win over Owen J.Roberts BOYERTOWN, Pa. - 
The Boyertown boys soccer team (8-2, 10-3) posted a 2-1 win over Owen J. Roberts (10-1, 13-3) on Wednesday night in Boyertown. The Bears are a game and a half back of the Wildcats for the PAC-10 Liberty division lead. 
Boyertown's Will Schul and OJR's Brandon Ott scored the first two goals of the game. 
Danny Yudt's goal with less than five minutes left in the game proved to be the difference. Quick Clicks
